WEBVTT

00:01.233 --> 00:03.202
Clarence:
Previously on "Clarence"...

00:03.204 --> 00:05.504
Belson, he...
put a bunch of [snickers]

00:05.506 --> 00:09.007
bags of manure
in Mr. Reese's room.

00:09.009 --> 00:11.176
And then -- [ Laughs ]

00:11.178 --> 00:15.580
And then, Miss Shoop,
he put manure in there.

00:15.582 --> 00:20.352
Oh, and then I told Jeff that
I would get his favorite drink.

00:20.354 --> 00:24.723
Belson put the cow poop
in there! [ Laughs ]

00:24.725 --> 00:25.790
[ Remote clicks ]

00:25.792 --> 00:27.359
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:30.397 --> 00:33.765
♪ I don't care what you say! ♪

00:33.767 --> 00:35.534
[ Thunder rumbles ]

00:35.536 --> 00:36.968
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:36.970 --> 00:39.037
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

00:39.039 --> 00:41.106
♪ I just can't wait ♪

00:41.108 --> 00:43.475
♪ Gonna have a sleepover ♪

00:45.379 --> 00:47.545
Excuse me, sir!
You have to pay for that!

00:47.547 --> 00:50.915
Mm-hmm. Nite Bites policy
dictates one cup per costumer!

00:50.917 --> 00:51.916
Oh, hey, Meg!

00:51.918 --> 00:53.552
Well,
fancy seeing you here!

00:53.554 --> 00:56.054
Oh, gosh,
- it's my second day on the job!

00:56.056 --> 00:58.256
I really think
I've found a home here.

00:58.258 --> 00:59.725
I mean I hope so,
at least.

00:59.727 --> 01:01.392
They even gave me the official
Nite Bites handbook

01:01.394 --> 01:03.729
Mm-hmm, it's like
a whole way to live.

01:03.731 --> 01:05.797
Oh, th-that's great, Meg.

01:05.799 --> 01:07.933
So you have
a lot of sunblock.

01:07.935 --> 01:09.434
Are you going on a trip?

01:09.436 --> 01:12.637
Well, I'm...
moving to California.

01:12.639 --> 01:14.473
[ Chuckles ]
- Oh, really?!

01:14.475 --> 01:18.476
Oh, that's really great,
uh, for you.

01:18.478 --> 01:21.079
I just feel so unneeded here,
you know?

01:21.081 --> 01:23.248
Am I...
- Am I even making a difference?

01:23.250 --> 01:25.083
You ever ask yourself that?
Yeah, I just --

01:25.085 --> 01:26.585
I think it's time for me
to just move on.

01:26.587 --> 01:28.654
Well, I guess not all of us
have that option.

01:28.656 --> 01:30.021
Well, this is not scanning.

01:30.023 --> 01:31.990
[ Door bell chimes ]
Hey, Miss Baker!

01:31.992 --> 01:33.592
Hey, Clarence!

01:33.594 --> 01:35.626
Hi, Jeff's mom!
Oh, hey, Clarence.

01:35.628 --> 01:36.661
[ Gasps ]

01:36.663 --> 01:37.996
You guys want to come
to my sleepover?

01:37.998 --> 01:39.798
Mmm, boop!
-[ Meows ]

01:39.800 --> 01:41.366
Kitties can sleep over, too!

01:41.368 --> 01:44.335
No, you know what, I can't.
- But why?

01:44.337 --> 01:46.170
I...
I already have plans.

01:46.172 --> 01:48.273
So, you know, that's it.
But, how come?

01:48.275 --> 01:50.609
Look, Clarence,
- it's really great to see you,

01:50.611 --> 01:54.312
but I -- I don't want to get
into the whole thing here, so...

01:54.314 --> 01:56.548
Why?
- I gotta hit the road!

01:56.550 --> 01:58.883
[ Gasps ]
Are you homeless!?

01:58.885 --> 02:00.785
Come sleepover
at my house!

02:00.787 --> 02:03.288
Ha, okay. Let me try it upside down.
Now we'll see if that works.

02:03.290 --> 02:04.790
Okay, just forget it.
I don't need it. Okay.

02:04.792 --> 02:07.025
You're still coming to my
sleepover, though, right?

02:07.027 --> 02:08.793
I've got it.
Let me check the manual.

02:08.795 --> 02:11.796
Can you slide your Nite Bites
card again for me?

02:11.798 --> 02:13.065
Meg, I don't have one.

02:13.067 --> 02:15.233
Let me get you
an application form!

02:15.235 --> 02:18.136
Yeah, yeah, that's
fine, just -- Hey.

02:18.138 --> 02:19.304
You have to pay for those,
yeah!

02:19.306 --> 02:20.972
[ Coughing ]
I was gonna!

02:20.974 --> 02:23.708
Hey, can I put 20 on pump two?
I've been waiting 10 minutes!

02:23.710 --> 02:25.477
Right after I get this.

02:25.479 --> 02:27.478
I just need gas here! Miss
Baker, come for the sleepover!

02:27.480 --> 02:28.680
It's gonna be the best sleepover
ever!

02:28.682 --> 02:30.815
-[ Growls ]
-Put the money on--

02:30.817 --> 02:32.650
-Ow!
-Come on.

02:32.652 --> 02:34.819
♪♪

02:34.821 --> 02:36.988
The light's off.

02:36.990 --> 02:39.324
Ugh, great.
[ Clicking ]

02:39.326 --> 02:41.426
The door won't open. Okay,
the power's out, okay.

02:41.428 --> 02:44.729
Um, I'm sure the manual
has an answer.

02:44.731 --> 02:45.997
Okay, okay.

02:45.999 --> 02:47.832
Step one --
check backup generator

02:47.834 --> 02:49.100
located in the backroom.

02:49.102 --> 02:51.002
-Ooh!
-This is insane.

02:51.004 --> 02:52.370
Let's just give her
a chance.

02:52.372 --> 02:54.539
I'm sure the power
will be back any second.

02:54.541 --> 02:59.410
♪♪

02:59.412 --> 03:01.213
-What?! What was that?!
-Huh?!

03:01.215 --> 03:03.081
Baker: We're saved!
- Clarence: It's Sumo's dad!

03:03.083 --> 03:04.349
[ All muffled ]
Let us out!

03:04.351 --> 03:07.686
Sumo? Hi, Sumo!
Hope you're okay.

03:07.688 --> 03:09.521
-Hello! Can you see us?
-Come on!

03:09.523 --> 03:10.522
Hi, Sumo, hi!

03:10.524 --> 03:11.890
Together: Oh!

03:11.892 --> 03:14.392
Bye, Sumo!
Bye, have fun!

03:14.394 --> 03:16.227
So I checked
- the backup generator, and --

03:16.229 --> 03:17.695
[ All gasp ]

03:17.697 --> 03:19.464
And turns out,
there isn't one.

03:19.466 --> 03:21.733
[ Groaning ]
Yay! Hooray!

03:21.735 --> 03:23.602
I mean, oh -- oh, no.

03:23.604 --> 03:26.805
And, F.Y.I., it is okay to snack
while we're in here,

03:26.807 --> 03:28.940
in moderation.

03:28.942 --> 03:30.909
Sick of moderation.

03:30.911 --> 03:34.245
[ Pen clicks ] And I
<i> will</i> be keeping tally

03:34.247 --> 03:36.448
and charging you
- when the power comes back on.

03:36.450 --> 03:39.917
That is enough!
I'm getting out of here!

03:39.919 --> 03:41.719
Out of my way, cupcake!

03:41.721 --> 03:44.590
Ma'am, ma'am, that mop
is Nite Bites property!

03:44.592 --> 03:45.791
One, two, three!

03:45.793 --> 03:47.559
[ Screams ]
Stop!

03:47.561 --> 03:49.461
I got to get out of this nacho
cheese place! No, no, no, no!

03:49.463 --> 03:51.729
Not today.
- I'm in charge here, people!

03:51.731 --> 03:54.098
Now if we could just [grunts]
stay indoors

03:54.100 --> 03:56.901
till further notice.

03:56.903 --> 04:00.138
She's gone completely bonkers.
Ha. I think she's funny.

04:00.140 --> 04:01.573
♪♪

04:01.575 --> 04:04.476
No, we're gonna be stuck
in here forever!

04:04.478 --> 04:07.245
Hmm. But we don't have to be
bad stuck.

04:07.247 --> 04:08.413
We can be...

04:08.415 --> 04:11.950
Fun stuck!
We have here a soda sofa!

04:11.952 --> 04:13.952
A tepee made of T.P.!

04:13.954 --> 04:15.587
Some happy birthday banners!

04:15.589 --> 04:16.822
When did you make
all this?

04:16.824 --> 04:18.590
While you guys
were just sitting around!

04:18.592 --> 04:21.960
Eh, okay, Clarence.
Whatever makes you happy.

04:21.962 --> 04:23.261
♪♪

04:23.263 --> 04:25.096
Well, hello!

04:25.098 --> 04:27.132
Spin 'em! Spin 'em!
Spin 'em!

04:27.134 --> 04:28.700
Spin 'em more!

04:28.702 --> 04:29.934
E.J.: And then...

04:29.936 --> 04:34.206
they called me up,
and hung me out to dry.

04:34.208 --> 04:36.641
It ruined my credit!

04:36.643 --> 04:37.609
[ Shrieks ]

04:37.611 --> 04:39.344
You were scared!
Nuh-uh.

04:39.346 --> 04:41.847
Yes-huh, you screamed!
No, I didn't.

04:41.849 --> 04:43.348
Five, six, seven, eight...

04:43.350 --> 04:45.850
Looks like you get
a mega-mansion.

04:45.852 --> 04:48.220
How come I got a shack?!

04:48.222 --> 04:50.522
Pillow fight!

04:50.524 --> 04:53.658
[ Grunting ]
- Whoo!

04:53.660 --> 04:54.826
[ Laughter ]

04:54.828 --> 04:57.729
Oh, wow! Okay, well,
that was not on sale.

04:57.731 --> 04:59.564
[ Grunting softly ]

04:59.566 --> 05:00.832
Joan Rivers
on the red carpet!

05:00.834 --> 05:02.333
You're right.
- Yes!

05:02.335 --> 05:03.668
[ Laughs ] Very nice job.

05:03.670 --> 05:05.637
Okay, this one's
my favorite movie --

05:05.639 --> 05:07.672
or it's one of them,
anyways. Okay.

05:07.674 --> 05:09.474
[ Grunting ]

05:09.476 --> 05:11.543
Jeff:<i> J-Proper</i>
<i>to Clarence-saurus.</i>

05:11.545 --> 05:13.811
Clarence,
is that a walkie-talkie?!

05:13.813 --> 05:15.013
Jeff:
<i>J-Proper to Clarence-saurus.</i>

05:15.015 --> 05:16.514
Oh, it's my Jeffie-talkie!

05:16.516 --> 05:18.083
Jeff, is that you, bud?

05:18.085 --> 05:20.185
[ Gasps ]
- Prank calls! Great idea!

05:20.187 --> 05:21.653
Perfect for a sleepover.

05:21.655 --> 05:25.323
Jeff, come in, Jeff.
Is your refrigerator running?

05:25.325 --> 05:26.657
We could use this to get out!

05:26.659 --> 05:28.893
We can use it
to check on our families!

05:28.895 --> 05:30.929
Jonathan, it's me!

05:30.931 --> 05:32.597
I'm trapped at Nite Bites.

05:32.599 --> 05:34.499
I'm here
with a bunch of normos.

05:34.501 --> 05:35.934
Get the chopper!

05:35.936 --> 05:38.102
Hey, stop that!
What is wrong with you?!

05:38.104 --> 05:39.503
I didn't do anything wrong.

05:39.505 --> 05:41.706
Yeah, hello?
Is any-- is anyone out there?

05:41.708 --> 05:43.341
Attention,
Aberdale residents!

05:43.343 --> 05:45.177
This is Melanie Baker, I--
Melanie, hey!

05:45.179 --> 05:46.611
What are --
what are you doing?

05:46.613 --> 05:49.180
Me and several other citizen's
are trapped

05:49.182 --> 05:50.715
inside 6400 North Adobe Way.

05:50.717 --> 05:53.584
Okay, we can't be using that
kind of unauthorized equipment.

05:53.586 --> 05:55.520
Is anyone out -- hear this?

05:55.522 --> 05:58.189
No! No, no, the handbook doesn't
mention anything like that.

05:58.191 --> 05:59.791
Yes,
but the handbook isn't--

05:59.793 --> 06:01.927
I'm sorry, but it's against company policy!
- No, don't.

06:01.929 --> 06:04.863
I can't lose my job over this, Melanie!
- This is crazy! We have to--

06:04.865 --> 06:08.066
Why don't you just go move
to California already!

06:08.068 --> 06:11.369
What?! That's right --
she's skipping town!

06:11.371 --> 06:13.205
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.
Moving to California!

06:13.207 --> 06:16.208
She doesn't care about any
of us -- never has, never will.

06:16.210 --> 06:20.946
You're leaving? No!
[ Sobbing ]

06:20.948 --> 06:23.048
You can't leave.

06:23.050 --> 06:24.883
Hey, Clarence?

06:24.885 --> 06:26.217
Go away, I'm in here.

06:26.219 --> 06:27.885
Someone's using the bathroom.

06:27.887 --> 06:31.889
Oh, Clarence, I didn't mean
for you to find out like this.

06:31.891 --> 06:35.560
I thought it would be
the easiest way, but...

06:35.562 --> 06:37.629
You're not leaving.

06:37.631 --> 06:39.564
Clarence,
you don't need me.

06:39.566 --> 06:42.133
You deserve a better teacher,
you know.

06:42.135 --> 06:43.768
I'm just
sort of burnt out.

06:43.770 --> 06:45.570
No, it's okay,
Miss Baker.

06:45.572 --> 06:46.737
I'll see you in class
on Monday!

06:46.739 --> 06:48.139
Is that crazy lady in there?!

06:48.141 --> 06:49.941
We can't find that...
What?!

06:52.946 --> 06:56.415
♪♪

07:04.758 --> 07:07.191
Hey! Did you guys
finish your sleepover?

07:07.193 --> 07:09.928
How did you get outside?

07:09.930 --> 07:13.598
Well, the mayor ate all our supply
of the Cheech's Popcorn Chips,

07:13.600 --> 07:16.100
so I had to take the sign
down -- 'cause you just can't

07:16.102 --> 07:19.170
expect us to advertise a product
we don't even have in stock!

07:19.172 --> 07:23.107
Then why
are we still in here?!

07:23.109 --> 07:24.475
I can't let you leave

07:24.477 --> 07:26.511
until I review
- the security footage myself

07:26.513 --> 07:28.146
and make sure
- no products were stolen.

07:28.148 --> 07:32.317
What're you talking about?!
To heck with your manual!

07:32.319 --> 07:34.853
[ Rock music plays ]

07:34.855 --> 07:35.954
Come for me.

07:35.956 --> 07:38.123
[ Growls ]

07:38.125 --> 07:40.392
We leave when I say we do.

07:43.396 --> 07:45.797
I am the captain now.

07:45.799 --> 07:48.633
Warm...cheese.

07:48.635 --> 07:50.368
[ Children laughing ]
[ Upbeat music plays ]

07:50.370 --> 07:52.803
♪ It's so cool in California ♪

07:52.805 --> 07:54.472
-Hey, Mel!
-Looking good, Mel!

07:54.474 --> 07:55.640
Oh, thanks!

07:55.642 --> 07:57.809
Nice hair, Mel!
Hang 10!

07:57.811 --> 07:59.677
Hey, cutie!

07:59.679 --> 08:00.645
Hi there.

08:00.647 --> 08:02.413
Can I use your oil goop?

08:02.415 --> 08:03.982
My what?

08:03.984 --> 08:05.816
Your oil goop.

08:05.818 --> 08:07.919
Can me and Clarence
borrow it?

08:07.921 --> 08:09.187
Ugh!

08:09.189 --> 08:10.755
We want to make a slide.

08:10.757 --> 08:13.724
Wait. You're the mayor.
Why aren't you helping us?

08:13.726 --> 08:15.893
Eh.
Eminent domain!

08:15.895 --> 08:18.329
Yoink!
All right, spread them!

08:18.331 --> 08:20.232
[ Giggling ]

08:20.234 --> 08:24.436
Julip: - Plus 31 bags of Cheech's
Fried Onion Jalapeño Popcorn Chips,

08:24.438 --> 08:26.671
plus 15 cans of Juicy G's --
no, wait, 16.

08:26.673 --> 08:28.373
Okay, now gotta start
all over again.

08:28.375 --> 08:31.042
Okay, five packs of gum plus --
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

08:31.044 --> 08:33.845
Okay, gotta grab
the "wet floor" sign.

08:33.847 --> 08:35.880
Hey, E.J., you ready
to get out of here?

08:35.882 --> 08:37.348
Heck yeah.

08:37.350 --> 08:40.385
So all we gotta do is trick her
into opening the door again,

08:40.387 --> 08:42.020
and then we just rush out
together.

08:42.022 --> 08:43.088
She can't stop us all!

08:43.090 --> 08:44.922
Right.
And that's when I make my move.

08:44.924 --> 08:46.925
No, Clarence,
- you don't need to do anything --

08:46.927 --> 08:49.060
just run out with us
when she opens the door, okay?

08:49.062 --> 08:52.430
Got it. Plus, I'll have
a little trick up my sleeve.

08:52.432 --> 08:53.731
No tricks, Clarence.

08:53.733 --> 08:55.433
It's a simple plan --
just run when we do.

08:55.435 --> 08:56.968
Okay.

08:56.970 --> 08:59.037
I have a secret plan.
Uh, Clarence!

08:59.039 --> 09:01.973
But, Mel, how do we get her
to open the door?

09:01.975 --> 09:04.709
♪♪

09:04.711 --> 09:06.310
You guys thirsty?

09:06.312 --> 09:08.579
[ Chugging ]

09:08.581 --> 09:11.215
[ Gulping ]

09:11.217 --> 09:12.951
[ Coughing ]

09:14.588 --> 09:17.088
Ugh!
It's not even cold anymore.

09:17.090 --> 09:19.991
[ Groaning ]

09:19.993 --> 09:21.426
Ugh! It's so sweet.

09:21.428 --> 09:23.328
Jeff really drinks this?

09:23.330 --> 09:25.496
[ Slurping ]
Yeah, it's his favorite.

09:25.498 --> 09:27.332
I saved him some.

09:27.334 --> 09:28.833
Mmm!

09:28.835 --> 09:30.935
Seems like the Slimy Raisin
Freezy is a huge hit!

09:30.937 --> 09:32.737
Oh, oops.
Gotta take down the sign.

09:32.739 --> 09:34.238
This is our chance!

09:34.240 --> 09:37.442
♪♪

09:39.746 --> 09:42.914
Oh, my!
Secret plan -- go!

09:42.916 --> 09:44.582
Clarence, no!

09:44.584 --> 09:46.350
Clarence, just --

09:46.352 --> 09:48.953
♪♪

09:48.955 --> 09:51.089
[ Chuckles ] Now we can just
keep having our sleepover

09:51.091 --> 09:52.323
forever and ever.

09:52.325 --> 09:54.759
And you don't even have to move
to California!

09:54.761 --> 09:56.427
You can just stay here!
-Out of the way!

09:56.429 --> 09:58.028
[ Grunts ]

09:58.030 --> 10:00.532
[ Groans ]
Too many chips.

10:00.534 --> 10:02.934
Let me through!
Wait! I almost got it!

10:02.936 --> 10:05.203
It's going to be
the best sleepover ever!

10:05.205 --> 10:07.439
[ All gasping ]

10:07.441 --> 10:08.506
[ Screaming ]

10:08.508 --> 10:10.274
[ Loud crash ]

10:10.276 --> 10:12.877
[ Coughing ]

10:12.879 --> 10:16.113
Julip: What is this?!
I have to clean all of this up!

10:16.115 --> 10:18.616
[ Grunting ]

10:18.618 --> 10:20.218
Somebody call for backup?

10:20.220 --> 10:21.786
[ Dramatic music plays ]

10:23.155 --> 10:24.055
Belson!

10:24.057 --> 10:26.390
Melanie?
I knew we'd find you!

10:26.392 --> 10:29.961
I'm so happy!
[ Sobbing ]

10:29.963 --> 10:31.663
What the heck is on your face,
Jim?

10:31.665 --> 10:33.498
Oh, no.
Okay, save the product.

10:33.500 --> 10:34.966
We have to save the product!

10:34.968 --> 10:37.535
The storm's getting worse!
We gotta get to the school!

10:37.537 --> 10:38.869
I should go down
with the ship.

10:38.871 --> 10:42.340
Meg, that is enough!
Come on!

10:42.342 --> 10:44.976
But I -- I swore an oath!
It's gonna be okay, Meg.

10:44.978 --> 10:47.345
A Nite Biter shall never
abandon their post

10:47.347 --> 10:48.546
under any circumstances!

10:48.548 --> 10:50.314
Just get in! Huh?

10:50.316 --> 10:52.984
Oh, no!

10:52.986 --> 10:54.752
♪♪

10:54.754 --> 10:56.487
Oh, wait, you're driving?

10:56.489 --> 10:57.822
Don't worry about it.

10:57.824 --> 11:02.060
[ Dramatic music plays ]

11:03.395 --> 11:05.230
♪ Early to bed ♪

11:06.766 --> 11:08.867
♪ Early to rise ♪

11:10.403 --> 11:12.337
♪ Picking my nose ♪
